In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4
servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low
simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry all produce.

Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites
from greens.

Dice @Fully Cooked Chicken Breasts{9%ounce} into bite-size pieces.

In a small #bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with as much @Sriracha{1%tsp}
and lime juice as you like.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add @Shredded Carrots{4%ounce} and scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally,
until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir chicken, @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tablespoon}, and @Sesame Dressing{1.5%ounce} into
pan with veggies. Bring to a simmer and cook until sauce is thickened and chicken
is warmed through, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

Remove pan from heat.

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in lime zest and @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4
servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with chicken stir-fry. Drizzle with sriracha
lime mayo. Sprinkle with scallion greens and as many @Sesame Seeds{1%tablespoon}
as you like. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

